title: Records for Presidio fatal collision 4/4/2023 (United States Park Police)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am requesting records of the US Park Police in relation to Northern District of California case 3:23-cr-00439-JD, specifically the April 4, 2023 incident involving a collision between a car driven by Arnold Kinman Low and cyclist Ethan Boyes in the Presidio of San Francisco. My request includes, but is not limited to, documents, incident reports, multimedia, body-worn camera footage, arrest filings, and other documentation linked to this incident. It also includes all documents, notes, correspondence, and memoranda evidencing sustained findings, reports, and investigations, and all communication and correspondence in whatever tangible medium between the officials, representatives of the victim or perpetrator, and the overseeing agency.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Bobbie Johnson
